{
  "stem": "8786.1",
  "chunk_idx": 8,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 8.0,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] It was-- somebody was-- I just heard this after the war that many, many years before I could remember they used to have a-- a-- the only thing which we had, it was a-- every Friday, the congregation gave out a newsletter giving us information about the services, what is happening around the synagogue, and so on.",
      "word_count": 61
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "Because Jewish life was concentrated around the synagogue.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "However, even though it wasn't a what you call today a very strictly [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] Hasidic town.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "It was not.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "There was seven, eight doctors.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And most of the people didn't even wear a beard.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "Most of the Jews of the town were intelligent, educated people.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "The rabbi of the town was an 84-year-old man.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "His name was Rebbe Balauity, B-A-L-A-U-I-T-Y.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Balauity.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "He was also-- he had probably the same-- the same story as with my grandfather.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "He was also taken away and sent to Auschwitz.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "It was-- they had young groups, boys.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "They had young groups for girls.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] This is besides the synagogue.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "We had a Jewish school in town.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "Besides the Hebrew school, we had the-- the secular school was also under Jewish auspices.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "It was the teacher was a Jewish lady, Ms.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "Brown.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "I even have one of her report cards which survived.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] And they had youth groups, I remember.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "They had even Zionist groups.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "They had a group, which is called the [NON-ENGLISH].",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "And I used to be invited to sing for them.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "I don't know why, but they called on me to sing.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "And they had-- around the synagogue, it wasn't active social life what you have here.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "For example, a European synagogue did not have the kitchen with a gas range, a Frigidaire.",
      "word_count": 16
    }
  ],
